                                                    Staff Information Page

   Joseph G. Benjamin, Soil Matrix

   Central Great Plains Research Station
   USDA-Agricultural Research Service, Northern Plains Area
   40335 Rd. GG
   Akron, CO 80720
   Phone: 970-345-0518 / 970-345-2259
   FAX: 970-345-2088
   E-Mail: jbenjamn@lamar.colostate.edu

   Education
          1989 Ph.D. Soil Physics, Iowa State University
          1984 M.S. Soil Management, Iowa State University

        1977 B.S. Agronomy, Iowa State University


   Professional Experience
          1982-1985 Teaching Assistant, Iowa State University
          1985-1991 Research Associate, Iowa State University
          1991-1996 Soil Scientist, Great Plains Systems Research Unit,
          USDA-ARS
          1996-present Soil Scientist, Central Great Plains Research Unit,
          USDA-ARS


   Research Interests
          Soil management effects on the soil environment for crop
          production
          Modification of soil physical properties by tillage
          Modelling tillage-induced changes in soil properties on plant
          production
          Alleviation of compaction by tillage


